  }
  pacing: "Pacing is fine, as the slower pace helps you sit with and get to know these characters"
  climax: "The climax is executed well"
  tone: "Tone feels like an artsy biopic"
  final_notes: "I saw the world premiere at the Austin Film Festival"
  overall: "Overall, a pretty good biopic on Japanese photographer Masahisa Fukase, as the film is a polished execution depicting the tortured artist; but the scenes with ravens are pretty unnecessary and draw away from the storytelling"
